description:
If you put your prayers into it, you can convey your magical power to someone
else. In the past, this act was apparently called "delivering your thoughts".
name: Rosary of Propagation
Synopsis
note:
<SG説明:A year after the \c[14]great war\c[0] that spanned the world, the protagonist
Celia arrived in the rural town of Variante, as if fleeing from the city area
that was attacked. There, she fell in love with a kind boy named Hayato and
spent her days looking for a chance to confess her feelings... Today, time flows
peacefully, a stark contrast to the time of the great war, but the Demon King's
army was plotting a \c[14]certain plan\c[0]. It was to eliminate the bloodline
of the \c[14]goddess\c[0] who was said to have saved the world in the past. The
bloodline of the goddess boasts considerable magical power. Therefore, they
released members of the succubus army, who are good at seducing people around
the world, and tempted those on the human side who are familiar with magic to
become spies. In Variante, the priest of the church became a target and fell for
Merill's charm. And finally, after a covert search... the first candidate for
the descendant of the goddess was found. It was the protagonist, Celia...
>

name: Regular Key
Sadi
note:
<SG説明:He is one of the executives of the Demon King's army and a great succubus.
Although he is chubby and not exactly handsome, for some reason, any "woman" who
comes into contact with him ends up being captivated. The reason for this is due
to his intense charm skill, unique to male succubi, which "completely steals the
interest of the women involved from anything other than him and instills love
for him". With this power, he turns women into his subordinates and trains them
to be experts in sexual activities, serving as combatants and spies. Thus, in
the great war, he never fought himself, but had beautiful women (sometimes
adventurers from the human side) as his close aides to protect him. Currently,
he is working with Merill on the orders of the Demon King to "deal with the
special bloodlines that have fled to various places". Here, Celia, a descendant
of the hero known as the goddess, is the target, and it seems that she was a
perfect match for him.
>

name: Merrill
note:
<SG説明:A succubus and a minion of Sadi. Her combat power is only about as strong as a
lower-class succubus, but she excels in cunning and has the power to win over
enemies with her sexual charm. She is a dangerous monster who continued to
confuse the human side with her specialty of temptation and espionage during the
great war a year ago. Like Sadi, she is good at gradually making her targets
obsessed with her, and she gets the ultimate pleasure when \c[27]the enemy
betrays and prioritizes her\c[0]. She has the cunning to use any means to obtain
that pleasure. In the aforementioned great war, \c[27]many men betrayed their
wives or girlfriends and secretly formed a mistress relationship with
Merill\c[0], and the information was leaked to the Demon King's army. Even now,
there are many men on the human side who continue to have a physical
relationship with Merill, and she is stealing confidential information from them
on Sadi's orders. Her ears are the same shape as the human race, so she doesn't
seem to be a congenital succubus...>

name: Celia
note:
<SG説明:The heroine of this work! She has a clumsy personality, but she tries hard to
make up for it. She doesn't have much magical power at the moment, but her
talent itself seems to be extraordinary (she's unaware of it). Originally from
Variente, she returned home when monsters invaded during the war. During that
time, she fell in love with Hayato, who was always kind to her. She has no
sexual experience, but she is quite interested, showing a surprisingly serious
side. In fact, Celia's appearance seems to be popular in town.
>

note:
<SG説明:Merill's best friend and the younger brother of the "Hero". He is a boy living
in Valiente, with a calm and quiet personality. He has provided various support
over the past year to help Celia, who came as an immigrant, to fit in here.
Although he has already passed away, he has the potential to become an
overwhelming warrior because his brother was a man who was called a "Hero" in
the great war \c[14]Hayato also has the potential to become an overwhelming
warrior\c[0]. Among them, he excels in abilities to support allies, such as the
defensive magic called \c[14]Protect\c[0] and \c[14]strengthening magic\c[0]. He
has almost no sexual experience, but he is secretly in love with Celia.....
>

name: Great War
note:
<SG説明:A war that broke out a year ago. The invasion by the monster side, controlled by
the Demon King, was carried out on a global scale, and the human side fought
back to stop it. \c[27]Due to our strategies being completely exposed\c[0] and
\c[14]the hero not being able to unleash the power of the holy sword that he
should have been able to use\c[0], we were forced to struggle more than
expected, and 30% of the world was invaded. As a result of this battle, the hero
died in a duel with a high-ranking officer of the Demon King's army. Celia, who
was a civilian, also took refuge in Variente because her city was occupied.
>

name: Unfinished Love Letter
Anthurium
note:
<SG説明:A mysterious talking doll. Its true identity is a spirit that possesses the
doll, and it seems to have been originally entrusted with the management of a
certain weapon in the church basement. However, the weapon is designed so that
only specific humans can touch it, and because no one who can do so has
appeared, it was questioning its own existence when it unfortunately caught the
eye of Sadi, who was planning to capture the descendant of the goddess. (Its
existence was revealed because the priest was seduced by Merill) As a spirit, it
has a strong resistance to magic, but its "Charming Gaze" and its naivety due to
being holed up in the church basement are its downfall, and it is seduced by
Sadi. It seems to be originally a kind-hearted entity, but now it has completely
turned into a pawn blindly in love with Sadi. It seems to be being used for its
burning passion and impulse towards the great succubus... Its gender seems to be
female.
>
